subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Meristic and morphometric characters are given in 
Tables 1–4
. Body elongate and compressed (
Figs.1
, 
2
). Head length 17.8–25.0% SL. Snout conical, length 25.4–34.5% HL (
Table 4
). Mouth terminal; maxilla extending well beyond anterior margin of eye (
Fig. 3
). Scales thin, deciduous; 37–40 lateral-line scales (
Table 2
), 23–25 predorsal scales, 16 circumpeduncular scales (
Table 1
). Dorsal-fin rays 9–10; anal-fin rays 14–16; pectoralfin rays 11–12; pelvic-fin rays 7–9. Anal and dorsal fins closer to caudal fin than to head. Origin of anal fin in front of origin of dorsal fin. Caudal fin deeply forked, rounded tips (
Fig.1
). Total vertebrae 39–41 (
Table 3
).
